Representative Emanuel Cleaver, Chairman of the Congressional Black Caucus, has expressed support for President Obama's address to Congress on job creation. Cleaver is pleased with the synergy between the proposal presented by the Congressional Black Caucus and the proposal submitted by President Obama. The proposal focuses on creating, protecting, and rebuilding jobs in America. Cleaver highlights the importance of modernizing schools, cutting defense spending, and being cautious with any proposed reforms to Medicare and Medicaid. The Congressional Black Caucus is committed to working with President Obama and Congress to address the jobs crisis and improve America's competitive edge.